In .NET 10, MAUI adopted Android's edge-to-edge rendering and `AdjustResize` was deprecated at the OS level. Here's the fix:

**Option 1 — Use `AdjustPan` (simplest)**

In `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
[Activity(WindowSoftInputMode = SoftInput.AdjustPan)]
public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity { }
```

This pans the whole window up so the focused input stays visible.

**Option 2 — Handle keyboard insets (recommended for chat UIs)**

Keep `AdjustResize` in the manifest and respond to insets in your layout. In your `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
#if ANDROID
builder.ConfigureMauiHandlers(handlers =>
{
    Microsoft.Maui.Handlers.PageHandler.Mapper.AppendToMapping("KeyboardInsets", (handler, view) =>
    {
        var activity = handler.PlatformView.Context as Android.App.Activity;
        var rootView = activity?.Window?.DecorView?.RootView;
        if (rootView == null) return;

        AndroidX.Core.View.ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(rootView, new KeyboardInsetsListener(handler.PlatformView));
    });
});
#endif
```

Then create the listener:

```csharp
#if ANDROID
using AndroidX.Core.View;
class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    private readonly Android.Views.View _view;
    public KeyboardInsetsListener(Android.Views.View view) => _view = view;

    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        _view.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, imeInsets.Bottom);
        return insets;
    }
}
#endif
```

**Option 3 — Disable edge-to-edge (quick escape hatch)**

In `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
{
    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);
    AndroidX.Activity.EdgeToEdge.Disable(Platform.CurrentActivity);
}
```

This restores .NET 9-era behavior but opts out of modern Android rendering.

---

**TL;DR:** `AdjustPan` is the quickest fix. For a proper chat UI where you want the message list to shrink (not scroll off-screen), use Option 2 with insets so only the bottom padding adjusts.
